# LAMMPS Input File
# Licensed under CC BY 4.0
# A Set of Materials-Science Tutorials for the LAMMPS Simulation Package
# Appendix: structure-analysis toolkit -- radial distribution functions
#
# Compute g(r) of diamond-cubic silicon (Stillinger-Weber) at three temperatures: room temperature, an
# intermediate temperature, and above the superheating limit, where the
# crystal melts during the run and the final sampling sees the liquid.
# A force-less pair_style zero is overlaid only to extend the neighbor
# list to 8.5 A so that g(r) covers several coordination shells
# independent of the force cutoff.  Outputs rdf_si_<T>.dat; plot all
# materials with rdf-plot.py.

variable T index 300 1000 2600

units metal
atom_style atomic
boundary p p p

lattice diamond 5.431
region box block 0 6 0 6 0 6
create_box 1 box
create_atoms 1 box
mass 1 28.0855
pair_style hybrid/overlay sw zero 8.5
pair_coeff * * sw Si.sw Si
pair_coeff * * zero

velocity all create $(2.0*v_T) 31415 mom yes rot yes dist gaussian
fix md all npt temp ${T} ${T} 0.2 iso 0.0 0.0 1.0
thermo 1000
thermo_style custom step temp pe press vol
run 10000

# sample g(r) over 10 ps
compute gr all rdf 250
fix rec all ave/time 100 100 10000 c_gr[*] file rdf_si_${T}.dat mode vector
run 10000

print "RESULT si T=${T} done"

clear
next T
jump SELF
